##Ridgway suffers from a shortage of patient samples, and "people's hope" was drowned out in 271 studies

As early as February 4, Gilead's 2,843 boxes of Radicivir had already arrived in Beijing, but now that people have heard that there are too few patients in the group, "people's hope" has been poured cold water.

Radzivir is the only drug currently considered by the World Health Organization to have the potential to fight the new coronavirus. "The hope of the people" was a homonym for Ridgeway's English name, Remdesivir, and also expressed the public's expectations for the drug.

At a Feb. 24 news conference, WHO Director General and Senior Adviser to Dr. Bruce Aylward said that Dr. Cao Bin of the China Japan Friendship Hospital, which is leading the clinical trial, said its program is now harder to recruit patients, not only is the number of cases declining, but many other, less promising studies are crowding out the trial.

A total of 168 patients with severe and 17 with mild illnesses are undergoing clinical trials of Radzivir, said Zhang Xinmin, director of the Biotechnology Center at the Ministry of Science and technology on Feb. 15. As part of the study design, the study will be carried out among patients with pneumonia who have been admitted to the COVID-19 and other hospitals. The first group of 761 patients will be enrolled, including 308 patients with mild to moderate illness, there were 453 patients in the intensive care group.

Clinical trials of the most promising new coronaviruses have fallen far short of what is needed. At the other end of the spectrum is the hustle and bustle: from January 23 to February 27,271 results were published in the COVID-19.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Medical staff lead a group of patients to practice Tai Chi Chuan at Dahuashan Shelter Hospital in Wuhan on Feb. 17. (source: Chinanews.com)

The rush of clinical research has robbed the Ridgeville trial of a large number of patients. Aylward urges that research projects that might be more promising be prioritised.

DEEPTECH has learned from a number of sources that the high threshold and numerous clinical trial runs of the Radzivir trial are a problem for Radzivir. So what happens to the Ridgeway study?

High threshold for entry

A case study of Redesavir in a clinical trial of severe new coronary pneumonia. The trial began on February 6,2020, and the study was completed on May 1,2020. This is a randomized, double-blind, placebo-controlled, multicenter phase III clinical trial.

The experimental scheme was divided into experimental group and Control Group. Patients in the study group were given a 200 MG loading dose of Radzivir on Day 1 and then 100 MG daily intravenously for 9 days; patients in the Control Group were given a placebo of 200 mg on Day 1 and 100 MG daily intravenously thereafter, continued treatment for 9 days.

There are seven criteria for inclusion, one of which excludes a subset of patients, who test positive for the new coronavirus with nucleic acid. For a variety of reasons, such as laboratory testing defects, some patients have multiple negative nucleic acid test, but the new pneumonia symptoms serious.

Another threshold in the inclusion criteria was that the time to onset was less than 12 days. In fact, many hospital inpatients are not in this time window, so can not meet this requirement.

The inclusion protocol requires patients to have not received any experimental treatment for the new coronavirus for 30 days prior to screening assessment. The requirement stopped many patients from taking certain drugs, such as Shuanghuanglian oral liquid, that had previously been recommended by officials or news reports. You know, the use of these drugs can add to the uncertainty of clinical research.

A person at Wuhan University People's Hospital said that in addition to the obstacles mentioned above, there was also the question of patients'own will, and some patients did not agree to join the group for the trial.

It was not clear whether the 68-year-old was being treated as part of the trial or as an emergency, according to official sources, who said the first patient to be admitted to the hospital with the disease began taking the drug on Feb. 6. Less than 200 were successfully recruited 10 days later. The number of recruits is unclear.

Still, the ridgway study offers new hope. On February 27th the Gilead Sciences announced the launch of two clinical trials for the treatment of COVID-19 pneumonia, recruiting 1,000 people worldwide. One of these randomized, double-blind, controlled clinical trials has been conducted at the University of Nebraska Medical Center. The first patient to be admitted was an American who had been evacuated from the diamond princess. The pilot scheme is slightly different from the Chinese scheme.

Urgent drug trials have been slowed by a lack of suitable patients, a major challenge in rapidly developing drugs during outbreaks. With the number of new infections dwindling in China, how much time do we have left for Redesivir?

A run on patients'resources

Among the 271 new coronavirus research projects registered with the http://www.chictr.org.cn/  , therapeutic clinical trials, diagnostic trials, intervention studies, observational studies, and epidemiological studies are included.

Of the 271 registered clinical trials for new pneumonia, both the Lopinavir and Ritonavir anti AIDS drug trials, there are also studies on cord blood Mesenchymal stem cell, convalescent plasma therapy, vitamin D for prognosis, Lianhua qingwen capsule, and diammonium glycyrrhizinate, there are even Taijiquan on patient Rehabilitation Studies, Health Qigong Yangfei Fang on patients with functional recovery and quality of life research, there are soybean water extract (soy milk) clinical treatment studies. Of course, there is also the well-known Shuanghuanglian oral liquid research.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Fig. : Clinical Study on the treatment of new coronary pneumonia by drinking soybean milk

Deeptech has learned that as many as seven clinical trials have involved more than 20 newly crowned patients in a section of Wuhan University People's Hospital. According to reports, the department's Ridgeville Project Group of only 2 patients.

At least nine projects are under way at Wuhan University People's Hospital, according to the China clinical trials registry. Including Lianhua Qingwen Capsule / Granule Treatment Trial 2(1 for suspected cases and 1 for confirmed cases) , hydroxychloroquine treatment efficacy study, nebulized inhalation Xiyanping injection treatment study, objective: to evaluate the efficacy of hydroxychloroquine in the prevention of new crown exposure among close contacts, risk factors of new crown pneumonia among health care workers, prevention and Control Strategy in hospital, characteristic changes of multiple organ ultrasound, and clinical trial of leflunomide. The most recent project, a clinical trial of recombinant Human Interleukin 2 for COVID-19 pneumonia, was registered on Feb. 24. The study has not yet been approved by the ethics committee, according to the China Clinical Trial Registry website.

A medical staff member at the People's Hospital of Wuhan University admitted that the number of patients was decreasing and that it was becoming more difficult for various projects to join the group.

Industry feedback is strong. On February 24, the Chinese Journal of Epidemiology published a group of Health Statistics and epidemiology workers, "on the scientific, standardized and orderly development of clinical trials related to COVID-19, " said the proposal, caution is required unless research is considered to be of great importance. Because the case backlog is the most, clinical most difficult time, is to reduce mortality, improve the cure rate of the critical moment, we should try to avoid interference to clinical treatment, avoid increasing the burden of clinical work.

The corresponding authors are Hao Yuantao of National Sun Yat-sen University, Tang Jinling of Guangzhou women and children's Medical Center, Jiang Qingwu of Fudan University and Li Liming of Peking University. They pointed out that the large number of projects and the number of patients can not meet the requirements of the study, which will make it difficult to obtain the expected results. If the sample size is insufficient and the selection of Control Group is unreasonable, the clinical study can not provide high-quality evidence of efficacy and safety, which makes the efforts of patients, researchers and management go down the drain.

Some experts question that many clinicians are not specialized in research. How much time do they have on the front line to actually do this research?

If this continues, institutions with the largest number of patients may end up with poor clinical results because those with the ability to conduct unconditional studies are unable to do so, the conditional ability insufficient person actually appropriates the patient resources for oneself.

What about Cao Bin?

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Photo | Professor Cao Bin, Director of the Radhiwe clinical trial and deputy director of the china-japan Friendship Hospital, explains the radhiwe project on Feb. 5. -SOURCEurXinhuanNewsnAgencyency)

What happens if it doesn't fit the original design? Cao Bin did not respond to a request for an interview.

Many views in the industry believe that the special period need not reduce so rigorous, operating difficulties in the design, you can consider the sample size and experimental design to make some concessions. Several academics have suggested that the ridgway project could consider relaxing recruitment criteria, increasing recruitment centres and extending recruitment times. For the former, consideration could be given not only to a 12-day time limit, but to a longer time limit. For the latter, we can add a shelter hospital as a recruitment center for light and moderate patients, and we can also consider increasing the number of patients outside Wuhan.

But the Chinese Journal of Epidemiology article did not endorse the idea of adjusting clinical research. "These ideas may have good intentions, but the result is often a lack of reliable conclusions, that is, irresponsibility to patients. ".

Li Tianquan, co-founder of the drug intelligence network, told DeepTech that now that the clinical trial plan has been determined, in principle it should be carried out strictly according to the registration plan, and the plan to be adjusted may cause a lot of trouble, for example, the pre-training of the cooperative hospital should be increased and so on.

Li suggested that administrative measures could be considered to prioritize the inclusion of more promising clinical studies.

One of the best results, of course, is that if Radzivir is effective, then a smaller sample can be persuasive. But given that NCP is a self-limited disease that can be cured without appropriate antiviral treatment, it weakens the case for a small study.

Dr. Wang Chenguang, a former professor at Peking Union Medical College who has worked on immunotherapy drugs, said the administration's efforts to interfere with the launch of clinical research programs were not promising. After all, the current national policy is to vigorously promote the development of traditional Chinese medicine, and the administration may be reluctant to delay some traditional Chinese medicine projects.

Modern medical standards need to be emphasized

Antony Foutch, director of the Institute of Medical Science at the NIH, said the United States urgently needed a safe and effective new treatment for pneumonia, randomized, placebo-controlled clinical trials are the gold standard for judging experimental treatments.

FOUTCH's gold standard is the stuff of modern medicine. Unlike traditional medicine, evidence based medicine does not rely on empiricism or past cases, and Randomized controlled trial is the primary source of evidence based medicine. Peking University First Hospital, for example, and Wang Guangfa, the chief of critical care medicine at the University of California, San Diego, who is prescribed the drug Lopinavitonavir, the drug has been recommended for trial by the COVID-19 in its second edition. However, in a study published in the Chinese Journal of Infectious Diseases, a team from the Shanghai Municipal Clinical Center for public health found no improvement.

Professor Li Yuping, founding director of the China evidence-based Medicine Center, said in a 2014 Bulletin of the World Health Organization that many people do not understand what evidence-based medicine is and question what it can do for China. Some of the clinical evidence produced in China does not meet international standards, mainly because there are not enough qualified researchers and there is not enough regulation of clinical trials. In 2007, Li youping led the establishment of the China Clinical Trial Registration Center, which became the first registration institution of World Health Organization's International Clinical Trial Registration Platform.

Evidence based medicine is already weak in China and is on the verge of total collapse in the face of a new and oppressive coronavirus, according to a recent media article, the collapse of evidence based medicine.

Many clinical trials, whether chemical or conventional, or plasma therapy for convalescent patients, fail to adhere strictly to medical principles. "Chinese Journal of Epidemiology" article also pointed out that because of the SARS period, we have enough lessons, can not make such mistakes. Ineffective Treatment does not mean no side effects, especially when the risk of ineffective drugs is not allowed to be passed on to the patient.

Ridgeway's research is one of the few projects that promises to stick with modern medicine. To be clear, Cao Bin's Ridgway study is registered with the Clinicaltrials.gov  .

A leading medical expert told DeepTech that Cao Bin's ridgway trial was a world class clinical study that recommended that he stick to a pre designed protocol with no changes to the entry criteria, even if the final research results are not convincing enough, but at least its findings can be used as the original basis for a second study.

If changes are to be made to the criteria, the expert said, it would be better to divide those who meet the strict criteria into one group and those who do not, so as to at least avoid the effects of inconsistent criteria.

Wang Chenguang also pointed out that a large number of patients in this epidemic were originally extremely precious medical resources. If they were not used properly, then medical resources would be wasted and the victims of the epidemic would be sacrificed, and the worst that can happen is that these misdeeds could be repeated the next time an epidemic strikes.
